Drake has broken his own record for the number of tracks to appear simultaneously on the Billboard Hot 100 chart.&nbsp; The Canadian hip hop star currently has a total of 24 songs on the chart dated April 8, Billboard reports. All 22 tracks from his most recent album release &#8220;More Life&#8221; are listed on the chart. The number one spot, however, is taken by Ed Sheeran&#8217;s hit single &#8220;Shape of You&#8221;.&nbsp; Drake can now lay claim to being the artist with the second-highest number of Billboard Hot 100 entries of all time, with a total of 154 tracks, behind the cast of the musical series &#8220;Glee&#8221;, who have scored 207 in total.-Relax news